	<text>
		<body>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_winer_mirka">Mirka Winer</persName> Testimony (doc. 301/1169)</p>
			<p>Original, manuscript, 4 pages, 210 x 295 mm, Polish language</p>
			<p><pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3011169_01.jpg"/>
				<orgName ref="#ehri_et_voivodships_historical_commission">Voivodship’s Historical Commission</orgName></p>
			<p>In <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublin</placeName></p>
			<p>On <date when="1945-11-15">15 November 1945</date></p>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_winer_mirka">Mirka Winer</persName></p>
			<p>Testifies for the record</p>
			<p>Born <date when="1932-02-04">4 February 1932</date></p>
			<p>Tatooed number A 3977 in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp">Auschwitz</placeName></p>
			<p><term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1214">Student</term></p>
			<p>Before the <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1080">war</term> she resided in <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/776252/belzyce.html">Bełżyce</placeName> near <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublin</placeName></p>
			<p>Presently in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublin</placeName>, <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">8 Lubartowska Street apt. 12</placeName></p>
			<p>Has mother; a merchant’s daughter</p>
			<p>Record taken by: <persName ref="#ehri_et_szajowicz_irena">Irena Szajowicz</persName>; Head of <orgName
					ref="#ehri_et_historical_commission_in_lublin">Historical Commission in <placeName
						ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublin</placeName></orgName></p>
			<p>I was living in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/776252/belzyce.html">Bełżyce</placeName> when <term type="subject"
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> entered Poland in <date when="1939">1939</date>. The commandant for the town
				was a <term type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">German</term> named <persName ref="#ehri_et_engel">Engel</persName>.
				We were terribly afraid of him, because he used to beat and <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532">shoot</term> people. He would invade a flat and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">kill</term> whole <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819">families</term>. That’s what happened to the <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_silbernadel">Silbernadel</persName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-820" type="subject">family</term>: father <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_silbernadel_kuna_herisch">Kuna Herisch</persName>, sons <persName ref="#ehri_et_silbernadel_usze">Usze</persName>
				and <persName ref="#ehri_et_silbernadel_jankiel">Jankiel</persName> for trading meat. He also stole and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-345" type="subject">plundered</term> Jewish flats. A few times a week
					<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1124" type="subject">gendarmes</term> would come from a neighbouring
				town 10 kilometres away – <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/764000/niedrzwica-duza.html">Niedźwice</placeName>. <note
					type="gloss">Niedrzwica</note>They had us give them money, autos, horses. They kept making new demands. It all started with a
					<q>contribution</q> of 20000 zlotys, and then they just kept demanding more. Once <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-men</term> came from <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/765876/lublin.html">Lublin</placeName> and took 400 men to <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-560" type="camp">Majdanek</placeName>, many people <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745">died</term> then, <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745">shot</term> by the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term>. In <date when="1941">1941</date> they took
				several hundred <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826">men</term> and <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825">women</term> to <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-560" type="camp">Majdanek</placeName>. One Tuesday in <date when="1942"
					>1942</date>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1126" type="subject">Ukrainians</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-men</term> came. They shot at people and took
				people away, <pb n="2" facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3011169_02.jpg"/> loaded them into <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522">train cars</term> and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-115" type="subject">transported</term> to <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2032" type="camp">Treblinka</placeName>. We stayed hidden, in a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">hideout</term> under the floor there was a pit. It was
				in my <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-822">cousin</term>’s flat. There were 50 people
				there. It was terribly stuffy, so stuffy that one 2-year old <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824">child</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term> of lack of air. The action went on for
				almost 2 days. After we went out, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-men</term>
				from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/764000/niedrzwica-duza.html">Niedźwice</placeName>, who were searching Jewish flats,
				caught us; they smashed furnaces, ripped off floorboards and so forth. We were locked up in a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-758" type="subject">synagogue</term>. After one day we managed to escape.
				Later, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-men</term> demanded 20000 per <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819">family</term> in return for making a <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> and not <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-532">killing</term> us but making us <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term>.</p>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_hess">Hess</persName> was the commandant. The <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> was fenced with wire and we were guarded
				only by <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-566" type="subject">Jewish militia</term>. <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_hess">Hess</persName> didn’t torment us too much. Almost 9 months later an <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-man</term> named <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_feix_reinhold">Feiks</persName><note place="bottom">Notorious SS functionary <persName ref="#ehri_et_feix_reinhold"
						>Reinhold Feix</persName></note>came with <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350"
					>Gestapo</orgName> officers. 500 <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term>
				and <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824">children</term> were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">killed</term> and the remaining 100 and the <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826">men</term> were taken to <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-561" type="camp">Budzyń</placeName>. I was saved because I mingled with
				the group who’d been <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">selected</term> to go.</p>
			<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_feix_reinhold">Feiks</persName> was commandant for the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term> in <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-561" type="camp">Budzyń</placeName>, where at that time there were already
				Jews from other towns: from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/767623/krasnik.html">Kraśnik</placeName>, even [from] <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/756135/warsaw.html">Warsaw</placeName>. There was a total of about 5000 of us. <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS-men</term> kept guard there. People <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term> every day. They <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745">died</term> of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-569" type="subject">hunger</term> (we were given a loaf of <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">bread</term> between 10 people; the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">soup</term> was thin and the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">potatoes</term> raw). From time to time <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">selections</term> took place; the weaker and the <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term> were <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">selected</term> and machine guns were fired. <pb n="3"
					facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3011169_03.jpg"/> Beforehand they had to dig their own graves, where the others buried them in later. <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-493" type="subject">Typhus fever</term> decimated people. I <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">worked</term> in the kitchen. <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825">Women</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">worked</term> in the <term type="subject"
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">German</term> estate and in ammunition and plane plants. <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826">Men</term>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">worked</term> in plants and built roads. Our plight
				was very miserable. <persName ref="#ehri_et_feix_reinhold">Feiks</persName> and an <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS Oberscharführer</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_mohr_otto">Mohe</persName> were especially cruel.</p>
			<p>A year later they dressed us in striped <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-836"
					>uniforms</term> and moved to a new <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">camp</term>
				named Barakenbau; it was located near <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-561" type="camp"
					>Budzyń</placeName>, but administered by <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-560" type="camp"
					>Majdanek</placeName>. <persName ref="#ehri_et_leipold_josef">Leipold</persName> was the commandant. He and <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS Unterscharführer</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_jungfleisch">Jungfleisch</persName> and <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216">Oberscharführer</term>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_kleist_wilhelm">Willi Kleist</persName> beat, shot and tormented us inhumanly. <persName
					ref="#ehri_et_leipold_josef">Leipold</persName>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">hanged</term> people head down from the barracks
				ceiling for any petty offence. The victims hung like this for several hours and many <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term> like this.</p>
			<p>Some time later we were moved from Barakenbau. I can’t put an exact date on <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-560" type="camp">Majdanek</placeName>. In <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-560" type="camp">Majdanek</placeName> I wasn’t all that miserable. When
				the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-004583">Red Army</orgName> approached, <term type="subject"
					ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> moved us to <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/774069/cmielow.html"
					>Ćmielów</placeName>; we <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-517" type="subject">walked</term> 170
				kilometres on foot. Those who couldn’t make it were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject"
					>shot</term>. For 8 days we were driven in rain with almost no <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832"
					type="subject">food.</term> In <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/774069/cmielow.html">Ćmielów</placeName> we were loaded
				onto <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522">trains</term> and taken to <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp">Auschwitz</placeName>. We had numbers embossed and wee
				directed to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> right away. I <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">worked</term> in <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-567" type="subject">lager</term>
				<note type="gloss">Lager – (Ger.) camp</note> B in <foreign xml:lang="de">Strassenkommando</foreign>. I <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">worked</term> very hard. I had claimed I was 16 to
				save myself. And so I had to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> like
				adults. They kept making <pb n="4" facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3011169_04.jpg"/>
				<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject">selections</term>, but I ran away every time. Later,
				in <date when="1944">autumn</date> there was a major <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-411" type="subject"
					>selection</term>. A lot of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">women</term> were
				sent to the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-499" type="subject">chamber</term>, and the rest – including
				me – [were] sent to <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-42" type="camp">Belsen Bergen</placeName>.<note
					type="gloss">Concentration camp <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-42" type="camp"
						>Bergen-Belsen</placeName> near <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/2910831/hannover.html">Hanover</placeName>.</note></p>
			<p>The journey took a week. In terrible <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-831"
					>conditions</term> and we suffered <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-569" type="subject"
				>hunger</term>. In <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-42" type="camp">Belsen Bergen</placeName> we
				lived in <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837">tents</term>. We would freeze terribly and
				get wet in the rain. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">Food</term> was scarce.
					<persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000228">Krämer</persName> arrived later on, as did <foreign
					xml:lang="de">Lagerältester</foreign>
				<persName ref="#ehri_et_starostka_stanislawa">Stenia</persName> from <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp">Auschwitz</placeName>, <note type="gloss"><persName
						ref="#ehri_et_starostka_stanislawa">Stanisława Starostka</persName>, <term
						ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-485" type="subject">capo</term> in <placeName
						ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp">Auschwitz</placeName> camp, promoted to Lagerälteste in
						<placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-42" type="camp">Bergen-Belsen</placeName>.</note> who was
				terribly cruel to us. [There were] plenty of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject"
					>SS-women</term> from <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp">Auschwitz</placeName> and
				they molested us very much, but I forget the names. We did not <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556"
					type="subject">work</term>. <persName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_pers-000228">Krämer</persName>
				introduced strict rigour and relations deteriorated to a state worse than in <placeName
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-0" type="camp">Auschwitz</placeName>.</p>
			<p>Next, we left with 500 <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825">women</term> to <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2850894/raguhn.html">Raguhn</placeName> near <placeName
					ref="http://www.geonames.org/2937959/dessau.html">Dessau</placeName>. We did very hard <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556" type="subject">work</term> in an ammunition plant there. <term
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-480" type="subject">Aufseherin</term>
				<persName ref="ehri_et_lanni">Lanni</persName> and <foreign xml:lang="de">Unterscharführer</foreign>, whose name I can’t remember,
				molested us dreadfully. <term type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_americans">Americans</term> were coming closer. We were
				loaded up onto auto and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-115" type="subject">transported</term> around
				for two weeks. They beat and kicked us terribly and gave almost no <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832"
					type="subject">food</term>. Finally, we arrived in <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_ghettos-449"
					type="ghetto">Theresienstadt</placeName> where we were to be burnt. There were 60000 people there. The commandant pledged with the
					<orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-419">Red Cross</orgName> to spare his and his <term
					type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825">wife</term> and <term type="subject"
					ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824">child</term>’s lives if he would disobey the order and not burn the
				people. The <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-419">Red Cross</orgName> took care of that and that’s how
				we were saved.</p>
			<p>[signature] <persName ref="#ehri_et_winer_mirka">Winer Mirka</persName></p>
